{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":6000,"text":"AIDS was discovered 1981; the virus, 1983."},{"time":11000,"text":"These Gapminder bubbles show you"},{"time":13000,"text":"how the spread of the virus was in 1983 in the world,"},{"time":17000,"text":"or how we estimate that it was."},{"time":19000,"text":"What we are showing here is --"},{"time":21000,"text":"on this axis here, I'm showing percent of infected adults."},{"time":28000,"text":"And on this axis, I'm showing dollars per person in income."},{"time":33000,"text":"And the size of these bubbles, the size of the bubbles here,"},{"time":37000,"text":"that shows how many are infected in each country,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and the color is the continent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"Now, you can see United States, in 1983,"},{"time":44000,"text":"had a very low percentage infected,"},{"time":47000,"text":"but due to the big population, still a sizable bubble."},{"time":51000,"text":"There were quite many people infected in the United States."},{"time":54000,"text":"And, up there, you see Uganda."},{"time":56000,"text":"They had almost five percent infected,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and quite a big bubble in spite of being a small country, then."},{"time":62000,"text":"And they were probably the most infected country in the world."},{"time":67000,"text":"Now, what has happened?"},{"time":69000,"text":"Now you have understood the graph"},{"time":71000,"text":"and now, in the next 60 seconds,"},{"time":74000,"text":"we will play the HIV epidemic in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77000,"text":"But first, I have a new invention here."},{"time":82000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":87000,"text":"I have solidified the beam of the laser pointer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"So, ready, steady, go!"},{"time":104000,"text":"First, we have the fast rise in Uganda and Zimbabwe."},{"time":108000,"text":"They went upwards like this."},{"time":110000,"text":"In Asia, the first country to be heavily infected was Thailand --"},{"time":114000,"text":"they reached one to two percent."},{"time":116000,"text":"Then, Uganda started to turn back,"},{"time":118000,"text":"whereas Zimbabwe skyrocketed,"},{"time":120000,"text":"and some years later South Africa had a terrible rise of HIV frequency."},{"time":124000,"text":"Look, India got many infected,"},{"time":126000,"text":"but had a low level."},{"time":128000,"text":"And almost the same happens here."},{"time":130000,"text":"See, Uganda coming down, Zimbabwe coming down,"},{"time":133000,"text":"Russia went to one percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135000,"text":"In the last two to three years,"},{"time":138000,"text":"we have reached a steady state of HIV epidemic in the world."},{"time":142000,"text":"25 years it took."},{"time":145000,"text":"But, steady state doesn't mean that things are getting better,"},{"time":148000,"text":"it's just that they have stopped getting worse."},{"time":151000,"text":"And it has -- the steady state is, more or less,"},{"time":155000,"text":"one percent of the adult world population is HIV-infected."},{"time":159000,"text":"It means 30 to 40 million people,"},{"time":162000,"text":"the whole of California -- every person,"},{"time":164000,"text":"that's more or less what we have today in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"Now, let me make a fast replay of Botswana."},{"time":171000,"text":"Botswana -- upper middle-income country in southern Africa,"},{"time":175000,"text":"democratic government, good economy,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and this is what happened there."},{"time":180000,"text":"They started low, they skyrocketed,"},{"time":182000,"text":"they peaked up there in 2003,"},{"time":185000,"text":"and now they are down."},{"time":187000,"text":"But they are falling only slowly,"},{"time":189000,"text":"because in Botswana, with good economy and governance,"},{"time":191000,"text":"they can manage to treat people."},{"time":194000,"text":"And if people who are infected are treated, they don't die of AIDS."},{"time":197000,"text":"These percentages won't come down"},{"time":200000,"text":"because people can survive 10 to 20 years."},{"time":202000,"text":"So there's some problem with these metrics now."},{"time":205000,"text":"But the poorer countries in Africa, the low-income countries down here,"},{"time":209000,"text":"there the rates fall faster, of the percentage infected,"},{"time":215000,"text":"because people still die."},{"time":217000,"text":"In spite of PEPFAR, the generous PEPFAR,"},{"time":220000,"text":"all people are not reached by treatment,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and of those who are reached by treatment in the poor countries,"},{"time":225000,"text":"only 60 percent are left on treatment after two years."},{"time":228000,"text":"It's not realistic with lifelong treatment"},{"time":232000,"text":"for everyone in the poorest countries."},{"time":234000,"text":"But it's very good that what is done is being done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"But focus now is back on prevention."},{"time":241000,"text":"It is only by stopping the transmission"},{"time":244000,"text":"that the world will be able to deal with it."},{"time":247000,"text":"Drugs is too costly -- had we had the vaccine,"},{"time":249000,"text":"or when we will get the vaccine, that's something more effective --"},{"time":252000,"text":"but the drugs are very costly for the poor."},{"time":254000,"text":"Not the drug in itself, but the treatment"},{"time":256000,"text":"and the care which is needed around it."},{"time":260000,"text":"So, when we look at the pattern,"},{"time":263000,"text":"one thing comes out very clearly:"},{"time":265000,"text":"you see the blue bubbles"},{"time":267000,"text":"and people say HIV is very high in Africa."},{"time":269000,"text":"I would say, HIV is very different in Africa."},{"time":272000,"text":"You'll find the highest HIV rate in the world"},{"time":276000,"text":"in African countries,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and yet you'll find Senegal, down here --"},{"time":280000,"text":"the same rate as United States."},{"time":282000,"text":"And you'll find Madagascar,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and you'll find a lot of African countries"},{"time":286000,"text":"about as low as the rest of the world."},{"time":289000,"text":"It's this terrible simplification that there's one Africa"},{"time":293000,"text":"and things go on in one way in Africa."},{"time":295000,"text":"We have to stop that."},{"time":297000,"text":"It's not respectful, and it's not very clever"},{"time":300000,"text":"to think that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"I had the fortune to live and work for a time in the United States."},{"time":309000,"text":"I found out that Salt Lake City and San Francisco were different."},{"time":313000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":315000,"text":"And so it is in Africa -- it's a lot of difference."},{"time":318000,"text":"So, why is it so high? Is it war?"},{"time":320000,"text":"No, it's not. Look here."},{"time":322000,"text":"War-torn Congo is down there -- two, three, four percent."},{"time":325000,"text":"And this is peaceful Zambia, neighboring country -- 15 percent."},{"time":329000,"text":"And there's good studies of the refugees coming out of Congo --"},{"time":332000,"text":"they have two, three percent infected,"},{"time":334000,"text":"and peaceful Zambia -- much higher."},{"time":336000,"text":"There are now studies clearly showing"},{"time":338000,"text":"that the wars are terrible, that rapes are terrible,"},{"time":341000,"text":"but this is not the driving force for the high levels in Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"So, is it poverty?"},{"time":346000,"text":"Well if you look at the macro level,"},{"time":348000,"text":"it seems more money, more HIV."},{"time":350000,"text":"But that's very simplistic,"},{"time":353000,"text":"so let's go down and look at Tanzania."},{"time":355000,"text":"I will split Tanzania in five income groups,"},{"time":359000,"text":"from the highest income to the lowest income,"},{"time":361000,"text":"and here we go."},{"time":363000,"text":"The ones with the highest income, the better off -- I wouldn't say rich --"},{"time":366000,"text":"they have higher HIV."},{"time":368000,"text":"The difference goes from 11 percent down to four percent,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and it is even bigger among women."},{"time":373000,"text":"There's a lot of things that we thought, that now, good research,"},{"time":377000,"text":"done by African institutions and researchers"},{"time":380000,"text":"together with the international researchers, show that that's not the case."},{"time":383000,"text":"So, this is the difference within Tanzania."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"And, I can't avoid showing Kenya."},{"time":387000,"text":"Look here at Kenya."},{"time":389000,"text":"I've split Kenya in its provinces."},{"time":391000,"text":"Here it goes."},{"time":393000,"text":"See the difference within one African country --"},{"time":396000,"text":"it goes from very low level to very high level,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and most of the provinces in Kenya is quite modest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"So, what is it then?"},{"time":404000,"text":"Why do we see this extremely high levels in some countries?"},{"time":408000,"text":"Well, it is more common with multiple partners,"},{"time":411000,"text":"there is less condom use,"},{"time":414000,"text":"and there is age-disparate sex --"},{"time":417000,"text":"that is, older men tend to have sex with younger women."},{"time":420000,"text":"We see higher rates in younger women than younger men"},{"time":423000,"text":"in many of these highly affected countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"But where are they situated?"},{"time":427000,"text":"I will swap the bubbles to a map."},{"time":429000,"text":"Look, the highly infected are four percent of all population"},{"time":433000,"text":"and they hold 50 percent of the HIV-infected."},{"time":436000,"text":"HIV exists all over the world."},{"time":439000,"text":"Look, you have bubbles all over the world here."},{"time":441000,"text":"Brazil has many HIV-infected."},{"time":444000,"text":"Arab countries not so much, but Iran is quite high."},{"time":447000,"text":"They have heroin addiction and also prostitution in Iran."},{"time":451000,"text":"India has many because they are many."},{"time":453000,"text":"Southeast Asia, and so on."},{"time":455000,"text":"But, there is one part of Africa --"},{"time":457000,"text":"and the difficult thing is, at the same time,"},{"time":459000,"text":"not to make a uniform statement about Africa,"},{"time":463000,"text":"not to come to simple ideas of why it is like this, on one hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"On the other hand, try to say that this is not the case,"},{"time":470000,"text":"because there is a scientific consensus about this pattern now."},{"time":474000,"text":"UNAIDS have done good data available, finally,"},{"time":477000,"text":"about the spread of HIV."},{"time":480000,"text":"It could be concurrency."},{"time":483000,"text":"It could be some virus types."},{"time":486000,"text":"It could be that there is other things"},{"time":490000,"text":"which makes transmission occur in a higher frequency."},{"time":493000,"text":"After all, if you are completely healthy and you have heterosexual sex,"},{"time":496000,"text":"the risk of infection in one intercourse is one in 1,000."},{"time":501000,"text":"Don't jump to conclusions now on how to"},{"time":503000,"text":"behave tonight and so on."},{"time":505000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":507000,"text":"But -- and if you are in an unfavorable situation,"},{"time":510000,"text":"more sexually transmitted diseases, it can be one in 100."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513000,"text":"But what we think is that it could be concurrency."},{"time":516000,"text":"And what is concurrency?"},{"time":518000,"text":"In Sweden, we have no concurrency."},{"time":520000,"text":"We have serial monogamy."},{"time":522000,"text":"Vodka, New Year's Eve -- new partner for the spring."},{"time":524000,"text":"Vodka, Midsummer's Eve -- new partner for the fall."},{"time":526000,"text":"Vodka -- and it goes on like this, you know?"},{"time":528000,"text":"And you collect a big number of exes."},{"time":531000,"text":"And we have a terrible chlamydia epidemic --"},{"time":533000,"text":"terrible chlamydia epidemic which sticks around for many years."},{"time":537000,"text":"HIV has a peak three to six weeks after infection"},{"time":540000,"text":"and therefore, having more than one partner in the same month"},{"time":543000,"text":"is much more dangerous for HIV than others."},{"time":546000,"text":"Probably, it's a combination of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548000,"text":"And what makes me so happy is that we are moving now"},{"time":551000,"text":"towards fact when we look at this."},{"time":553000,"text":"You can get this chart, free."},{"time":555000,"text":"We have uploaded UNAIDS data on the Gapminder site."},{"time":558000,"text":"And we hope that when we act on global problems in the future"},{"time":562000,"text":"we will not only have the heart,"},{"time":565000,"text":"we will not only have the money,"},{"time":567000,"text":"but we will also use the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}